 2010 }}, ''[[News24]]'' (January 26, 2010)</ref>\n|-\n|Spes Bona High School\n|[[Cape Town]], South Africa\n|May 14, 2013\n|1\n| 17-year-old Enrico Martin was shot in the head while he was entering Spes Bona High School. He later died in a hospital. Authorities believe that the attack was gang-related. No arrests have been made.<ref name=southafricaiolnews>{{cite web|title=Schoolboy knifed: pupils describe attack|url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/crime-courts/schoolboy-knifed-pupils-describe-attack-1.1586895#.UlICFYaUTOU|publisher=[[IOL News]]|date=October 4, 2013|accessdate=October 6, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pupil dies after school shooting|work=EWN|date=May 14, 2013|url=http://ewn.co.za/2013/05/15/Grant-condemns-school-shooting|accessdate=October 6, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Yobe State school shooting]]\n|Mamudo, [[Nigeria]]\n|July 6, 2013\n|42\n|42 people were fatally shot while 6 were injured.\n|-\n| [[Garissa University College attack]]\n| [[Garissa]], [[Kenya]]\n| April 3, 2015\n| 147\n| Somali Al-Shabaab militants killed 147 students at Garissa University College.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2015/04/03/africa/kenya-garissa-university-attack-witnesses/|title=Inside Garissa University College dorm's scene of slaughter |publisher=[[CNN News]] |date=April 3, 2015}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Asia===\nThe following is a list of incidents of shootings that occurred in schools in Asia.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Name\n! Location\n! Date\n! Death toll\n! class = \"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|Li Shing Junior High School || [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] || January 26, 1962 || 7 || Tsui Yin, a 41-year-old former physical education teacher at Li Shing junior high school in Taipei, shot and killed the principal, the principal's wife and five other faculty members with a pistol, in revenge for his dismissal. He wounded three others, among them the principal's daughter, before escaping in a taxi. He was arrested and sentenced to death.<ref>Admits killing 7 for revenge, ''[[Pacific Stars and Stripes]]'' (January 27, 1962)</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=H2gUAAAAIBAJ&sjid=KQEEAAAAIBAJ&pg=7282,775520&dq= Teacher who slew 7 denied wish to see pupil perform], ''[[Toledo Blade]]'' (July 26, 1962)</ref>\n|-\n|[[Ma'alot massacre]] || [[Ma'alot]], Israel || May 15, 1974 || 25 ||The Ma'alot massacre was a terrorist attack carried out by the [[Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine]] at the Netiv Meir elementary school in the town of Ma'alot. It included a two-day hostage-taking of 115 people which ended in the deaths of over 25 hostages.\n|-\n|[[Sana'a massacre]] || [[Sana'a]], [[Yemen]] || March 30, 1997 || 8 ||The Sana'a massacre was a school massacre that occurred in Sana'a, Yemen. [[Mohammad Ahman al-Naziri]], 48, attacked hundreds of pupils at two schools, killing six children and two adults with an assault rifle. Naziri, whose five children attended the Tala'i school, alleged that one of his daughters had been raped by the school administrator. No evidence was found of this. Naziri was [[capital punishment|sentenced to death]] the next day and executed on April 5, 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aparchive.com/metadata/Yemen-Gunman-goes-on-shooting-spree-in-schools/4f98c1db2448fa0b66a50800f77971ac|title=Yemen \u2013 Gunman goes on shooting spree in schools \u2013 AP Archive|website=Aparchive.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[UP Sigma Rho#Related violence|University of the Philippines shooting]] || [[Quezon City]], Philippines || February 19, 1999 || 1 || A student was shot dead by a [[Fraternities and sororities|fraternity]] member after being mistaken for a member of a rival fraternity.{{Citation needed |date=October 2012}}\n|-\n|Longzhou County Middle School shooting || [[Longzhou County]], China || October 19, 1999 || 1 (the perpetrator) || After spending the afternoon drinking, school guard Liang Yongcheng walked into a students' dormitory at a middle school in Longzhou county and threatened to kill everybody who tried to stop him. He eventually committed suicide, but not before shooting a teacher and six students with a hunting rifle.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/445517051.html?dids=445517051:445517051&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+26%2C+1999&author=&pub=Daily+Mercury&desc=School+guard+injures+seven+in+shooting+spree&pqatl=google School guard injures seven in shooting spree], ''[[Guelph Mercury]]'' (October 26, 1999) {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107072110/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/445517051.html?dids=445517051:445517051&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+26,+1999&author=&pub=Daily+Mercury&desc=School+guard+injures+seven+in+shooting+spree&pqatl=google |date=November 7, 2012 }}</ref>\n|-\n|Number 34 Middle School || [[Lanzhou]], China ||September 26, 2002 || 2 (including the perpetrator) || Yang Zhengming, who worked as a mini-bus driver for Number 34 Middle School in Lanzhou, killed a teacher and wounded two others at the school with a hunting rifle, one of the wounded being his former girlfriend. Police finally shot him dead after negotiating with him for two hours while he was standing on the roof and threatening to commit suicide.<ref>[http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/en/doc/2002-09/27/content_138081.htm Two dead in school shooting in northwest China city] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021225503/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/en/doc/2002-09/27/content_138081.htm |date=October 21, 2012 }}, ''[[China Daily]]'' (September 27, 2002)</ref><ref>[http://muzi.com/cc/english/10351,19931.shtml?m=4&q=1227401 Driver shoots teacher in China campus killing] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714141206/http://muzi.com/cc/english/10351%2C19931.shtml?m=4&q=1227401 |date=July 14, 2011 }}, ''muzi.com'' (September 27, 2002)</ref>\n|-\n| [[Pak Phanang school shooting]] || [[Nakhon Si Thammarat]], [[Thailand]] || June 6, 2003 || 2 || 17-year-old Anatcha Boonkwan killed two and injured four of his fellow students after losing a fist-fight with one of his classmates.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=South China Morning Post |url=http://www.scmp.com/article/441323/gangs-not-only-schoolyard-killers |title=GANGS NOT THE ONLY SCHOOLYARD KILLERS |first=Jason |last=Gagliardi |date=January 15, 2004 |accessdate=December 18, 2012 }}</ref>\n|-\n| Niutoushan Primary School shooting || [[Guangde County]], China || October 5, 2005 || 0 || 18 people, among them 16 children, were injured when Liu Shibing shot them with six home-made guns at Niutoushan Primary School in Guangde.<ref>[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-10/13/content_3612562.htm 18 people wounded in school shooting in Anhui], ''[[Xinhua]]'' (October 13, 2005) {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107223033/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-10/13/content_3612562.htm |date=November 7, 2012 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Beirut Arab University shooting]] || [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]] || January 25, 2007 || 4 || Four people were shot dead in clashes between pro- and anti-government activists, and about 200 were hurt in the violence that flared after a scuffle between students at a Beirut university. The opposition accused the government camp of starting the riots and the four dead included two Hezbollah students, who were fired at from rooftops.{{Citation needed |date=October 2012}}\n|-\n|[[Euro International school shooting]] || [[Gurgaon]], India || December 12, 2007 || 1 || A shooting occurred at Euro International, a private secondary school in Gurgaon, Haryana, India. The gunmen were students 14-year-old Akash Yadav{{Citation needed |date=January 2014}} and 13-year-old Vikas Yadav{{Citation needed |date=January 2014}}, who shot and killed a 14-year-old student.<ref>[http://in.reuters.com/article/2007/12/11/idINIndia-30933320071211 Boy shoots classmate dead in Gurgaon school], ''[[Reuters]]'' (December 11, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n|[[Mercaz HaRav shooting]]|| [[Jerusalem]], Israel || March 6, 2008 || 9 (including the perpetrator) || Alaa Abu Dhein, an [[Israeli Arab]]ic yeshiva bus driver, entered the Mercaz HaRav yeshiva with guns blazing, killing eight and wounding seven, before being shot dead himself by a part-time student. This incident, as do many massacres in the [[Levant]], soon took on racial and religious overtones, pitting Palestinians and Israeli Arabs against Jews.<ref>\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/middle_east/7282269.stm Eight killed at Jerusalem school]\", BBC News Online, March 6, 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.nationalterroralert.com/updates/2008/03/06/terror-attack-at-jerusalem-seminary-merkaz-harav-yeshiva-8-dead/ Terror Attack At Jerusalem Seminary \u2013 Merkaz HaRav Yeshiva \u2013 8 Dead] National Terror Alert Response Center, March 6, 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.upi.com/NewsTrack/Top_News/2008/03/06/jerusalem_seminary_attacked/8267/ Jerusalem seminary attacked] UPI, March 6, 2008 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080308201142/http://www.upi.com/NewsTrack/Top_News/2008/03/06/jerusalem_seminary_attacked/8267/ |date=March 8, 2008 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Azerbaijan State Oil Academy shooting]] || [[Baku]], Azerbaijan || April 30, 2009 || 13 (including the perpetrator) || 29-year-old Farda Gadirov opened fire with a [[Makarov PM]] semi-automatic pistol inside the school building of [[Azerbaijan State Oil Academy]], killing 12 people, and wounding 13 others. He committed suicide by shooting himself in the head.<ref name=\"cnn\">{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/europe/04/30/azerbaijan.shooting/index.html?iref=mpstoryview|agency=[[CNN.com]]|title=Azerbaijan gunman kills 12 at university|date=April 30, 2009|accessdate=April 30, 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090503035758/http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/europe/04/30/azerbaijan.shooting/index.html?iref=mpstoryview| archivedate= May 3, 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://iansa.org/campaigns_events/Baku_30Apr09.htm |title=Academy mass shooting |date=April 30, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101215090929/http://iansa.org/campaigns_events/Baku_30Apr09.htm |archivedate=December 15, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azadliq.org/content/article/1619275.html|publisher=Azadliq.org|title= Ekspert basq\u0131nda \"Makarov\" dan istifad\u0259 olunmas\u0131na \u015f\u00fcbh\u0259 edir|date=April 30, 2009|accessdate=May 3, 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090503163319/http://www.azadliq.org/content/article/1619275.html| archivedate= May 3, 2009 | url-status= live|language=az}}</ref>\n|-\n|Xuwen school shooting || [[Xuwen]], [[Guangdong]], China || October 27, 2011 || 1 || A 16-year-old student was shot and killed at the entrance gate of a public school.<ref>\"[http://ireport.cnn.com/docs/DOC-695300]\", CNN, October 27, 2011</ref><ref>\"[http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_4e780db10102dtlb.html]\", Sina, October 27, 2011. (in Chinese)</ref>\n|-\n|[[2014 Peshawar school attack]] || [[Peshawar]], Pakistan || December 16, 2014 || 145 || A group of nine [[Taliban]] gunmen stormed the [[Army Public School Peshawar|Army Public School]], shooting and lobbing grenades.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/17/world/asia/taliban-attack-pakistani-school.html|title=Pakistani Taliban Attack on Peshawar School Leaves 145 Dead|last=Walsh|first=Declan|newspaper=New York Times|date=December 17, 2014|accessdate=December 17, 2014}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Canada===\nThis article is listed in chronological order and provides additional details of incidents in which a firearm was discharged at a school in Canada, including incidents of shootings on a school bus. Mass killings in Canada are covered by a [[List of massacres in Canada]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Name !! Location !! Date !! Year !! Death toll !! Notes\n|-\n|Markdale School shooting || [[Markdale, Ontario]] || August 25 || 1884 || 1 (the perpetrator) || The 28-year-old head teacher, William Norris wounded Fanny Ford, a teacher who had rejected his advances, with three shots. He then fatally shot himself through the head.<ref>{{cite book|last=Hubbert|first=Mildred Young|title=Markdale, the Crossroads of Grey |year=1988|publisher= Markdale Historical Society|location=Canada|isbn=978-0-9693531-0-2|pages=79}}</ref><ref>Markdale Standard (Markdale, Ont.), August 28, 1884, p. 4, column 1</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.ourontario.ca/ghpl/1123032/data|title=Norris, M. (Died on 25 Aug 1884)|first1=Grey|last1=Highl}}</ref>\n|-\n|Kingston School shooting || [[Kingston, Ontario]] || April 28 || 1902 || 1 || Beatrice Holland, a 14-year-old student, is shot and killed by a fellow student at the Frontenac School. The shooter, 15-year-old Eric Sharp, fled the scene but later turned himself in to the police.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.ca/newspapers?id=nUouAAAAIBAJ&sjid=tX4FAAAAIBAJ&pg=6854,2114367&dq=school+tragedy&hl=en |title=Shot By Schoolmate Frontenac School, Kingston, Scene of a Tragedy. Boy Killed Girl Pupil |publisher=News.google.ca |date=April 29, 1902 |accessdate=October 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|Altona schoolhouse shooting || [[Altona, Manitoba]] || October 10 || 1902 || 2 (including the perpetrator) || Henry J. Toews, a schoolteacher, confronted on the road three school trustees with whom he had some problems, drew a revolver, and shot all of them. Toews then returned to the schoolhouse and shot three female students who were the children of the trustees before turning the gun on himself. One of the students died and the shooter died months later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://manitobia.ca/resources/books/local_histories/081.pdf|title=Manitobia|website=Manitobia.ca|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://spectatortribune.com/the-altona-school-shooting-of-1902/|title=The Altona school shooting of 1902 \u2013 Spectator Tribune|date=March 15, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Ross Sheppard High School#Incidents|Ross Sheppard High School shooting]] || [[Edmonton]], [[Alberta]] || March 16 || 1959 || 1 || 19-year-old Stan Williamson opened fire with a .22 caliber rifle inside a crowded corridor of Ross Sheppard High School, killing 16-year-old Howard Gates and wounding five teenage girls. The shooting ended when three 18-year-old students held the gunman down until he could be arrested by police.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yegishome.ca/homes|title=Homes for Sale in Edmonton|website=YEGisHome.ca|access-date=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825003907/http://yegishome.ca/homes|archive-date=August 25, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Centennial Secondary School shooting]] || [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]] || May 28 || 1975 || 3 (including the perpetrator) || 16-year-old gunman Michael Slobodian shot and killed a fellow student and a teacher, and injured 13 other students before turning the gun on himself and committing suicide in a school hallway.<ref name=\"STAR_1975_2007\">{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/News/article/217023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071123144450/http://www.thestar.com/News/article/217023 |url-status=dead |archive-date=November 23, 2007 |title=Shooting violence in Canadian schools 1975\u20132007 |date=May 23, 2007 | location=Toronto |work=The Star}}</ref> Slobodian is the first recorded high-school aged school shooter in the country.\n|-\n|[[St. Pius X High School shooting]] || [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]] || October 27 || 1975 || 3 (including the perpetrator) || Robert Poulin, an 18-year-old St. Pius student, opened fire on his classmates with a shotgun, killing one and wounding five before turning the gun on himself and committing suicide. Poulin had raped and stabbed his 17-year-old friend Kim Rabot to death prior to the shooting. A book entitled ''Rape of a Normal Mind'' was written about the incident.<ref name=\"STAR_1975_2007\"/>\n|-\n|Sturgeon Creek High School Shooting<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/local/when-school-shootings-were-unthinkable-187569241.html|title=When school shootings were unthinkable|newspaper=Winnipeg Free Press|date=January 19, 2013|last1=Martin|first1=Nick}}</ref> || [[Winnipeg]], [[Manitoba]] || October || 1978 || 1 || A 17-year-old student shot a 16-year-old to death, allegedly for ridiculing the American rock band [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]{{Citation needed|date=September 2015}}. He was arrested and found not guilty of first-degree murder by reason of insanity.<ref name=\"STAR_1975_2007\"/>\n|-\n|[[Weston Collegiate Institute]] || [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] || || 1989 || 0 || The school principal escorted a group of trespassers off school property. They returned an hour later and when confronted by the principal a male (19) shot at him while fleeing the property. No one was injured. A fence around the perimeter was later erected due to this incident.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=sLebV_ZIOXMC&pg=PA112&lpg=PA112&dq=weston+collegiate+toronto+school+shooting#v=onepage&q=weston+collegiate+toronto+school+shooting&f=false|title=School Shootings: Mediatized Violence in a Global Age|first1=Glenn W.|last1=Muschert|first2=Johanna|last2=Sumiala|date=November 26, 2012|publisher=Emerald Group Publishing|via=Google Books|isbn=9781780529196}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]] || [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]] || December 6 || 1989 || 15 (including the perpetrator) || 25-year-old [[Marc L\u00e9pine]], armed with a legally obtained [[semi-automatic rifle]] and a [[hunting knife]], embarked on a shooting spree throughout the school, killing fourteen women and injuring ten other women and four men before killing himself.<ref name=\"STAR_1975_2007\"/>\n|-\n|[[Concordia University massacre]] || [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]] || August 24 || 1992 || 4 || Dr. [[Valery Fabrikant]], a 52-year-old former associate professor of mechanical engineering at Concordia, shot and killed four of his ex-colleagues and wounded a fifth before being subdued by two people he took hostage and being arrested by police.<ref name=\"STAR_1975_2007\"/>\n|-\n|[[W. R. Myers High School shooting]] || [[Taber, Alberta]] || April 28 || 1999 || 1 || A 14-year-old student, Todd Cameron Smith, walked into his school and randomly shot at three students, killing one named Jason Lang and injuring another before being arrested.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/1999/04/28/alberta990428.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070522210646/http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/1999/04/28/alberta990428.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=May 22, 2007 |title=One dead, one wounded in Alberta school shooting |newspaper=[[CBC News]] |date=November 10, 1999}}</ref> This shooting took place only eight days after the [[Columbine High School massacre]] and is widely believed to have been a [[copycat crime]].\n|-\n|[[Bramalea Secondary School]] || [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]] || December 10 || 2004 || 1 || On December 10, 2004, a gunman shot 47-year-old grade 10 teacher Aysegul Candir in the head multiple times in a Bramalea Secondary School parking lot. Mrs. Candir was pronounced dead in hospital later in the day.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mitchell|first1=Bob|title=Wife lived in fear, murder trial told|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/2007/01/23/wife_lived_in_fear_murder_trial_told.html|publisher=thestar.com|accessdate=August 31, 2016|date=January 23, 2007}}</ref> Peel Regional Police would later apprehend Candir's 62-year-old husband, Erhun, and charge him with murder. The incident was considered as a domestic dispute, and even though the school was locked down for most of the day, students were never in harm's way.\n|-\n|[[Dawson College shooting]] || [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]] || September 13 || 2006 || 2 (including the perpetrator) || 25-year-old [[Kimveer Gill]] began shooting outside the de Maisonneuve Boulevard entrance to the school, hitting several students and visitors, and moved towards the atrium by the cafeteria on the main floor, where he shot dozens of additional victims.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Montreal Killer Was a Death-Obsessed Goth |newspaper=Toronto Daily News |date=September 14, 2006 |url=http://www.torontodailynews.com/index.php/WorldNews/2006091420montreal-gunman |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090224132524/http://www.torontodailynews.com/index.php/WorldNews/2006091420montreal-gunman |archivedate=February 24, 2009 |accessdate=September 15, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Two gunmen open fire at Dawson College |newspaper=[[The Gazette (Montreal)|The Gazette]] |date=September 13, 2006 |url=http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/story.html?id=6332c17e-c92a-4427-a98d-4678301674e3 |accessdate=September 13, 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061021021906/http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/story.html?id=6332c17e-c92a-4427-a98d-4678301674e3 |archivedate=October 21, 2006 }}</ref> The shooter later committed suicide by shooting himself in the head after being shot in the arm by police.<ref>{{cite news|title=Montreal gunman killed himself: autopsy |newspaper=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] |date=September 14, 2006 |url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/09/14/qc-dawsoninvestigation.html |accessdate=September 15, 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107204516/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/09/14/qc-dawsoninvestigation.html |archivedate=November 7, 2012 }}</ref> One victim died at the scene, while another 19 were injured, eight of whom were listed in critical condition with six requiring surgery.<ref>{{cite press release |publisher=Service de police de la ville de Montr\u00e9al |date=September 13, 2006 |title=Communiques |url=http://www.spvm.qc.ca/fr/documentation/3_1_2_communiques.asp?nocomm=389}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Update 7 \u2013 Gunman kills one, wounds 19 at Montreal college |work=[[Reuters]] |date=September 13, 2006 |url=http://today.reuters.com/news/articlebusiness.aspx?type=tnBusinessNews&storyID=nN13394701 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080204004211/http://today.reuters.com/news/articlebusiness.aspx?type=tnBusinessNews&storyID=nN13394701 |archivedate=February 4, 2008 |accessdate=September 14, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Woman, gunman dead in Montreal school rampage |newspaper=[[CBC News]] |date=September 13, 2006 |url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/09/13/shots-dawson.html |accessdate=September 13, 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061023204014/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/09/13/shots-dawson.html |archivedate=October 23, 2006 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[C. W. Jefferys Collegiate Institute shooting]] || [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] || May 23 || 2007 || 1 || Two 17-year-old Canadian citizens, whom the media can not identify under the provisions of Canada's [[Youth Criminal Justice Act]], were arrested on May 27, 2007, and charged with the first-degree murder of a 15-year-old student at the [[C. W. Jefferys Collegiate Institute]]. Prior to one of the arrests, police had taken the unusual step of obtaining a judicial order to publish one suspect's name and photograph as he was considered armed and dangerous. The media reported his identity and photo, then had to take the stories off their websites after he was arrested hours later.<ref name=\"STAR_1975_2007\"/>\n|-\n|[[Bendale Business and Technical Institute#In the news|Bendale Business and Technical Institute shooting]] || [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] || September 16 || 2008 || 0 || A 16-year-old boy was shot in the chest in the school's parking lot following an altercation involving several people. The victim was hospitalized in critical condition. On September 17, 2008, Toronto Police announced it had made two arrests in the case; 18-year-old Mark Deicsics was charged with armed robbery.<ref name=\"Bendale\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/school-shooting-france-high-school-grasse-1.4027457 |title=Teen shot, injured at Canadian high school |work=[[USA Today]] |date=September 16, 2008 |accessdate=May 7, 2013 }}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=October 2018}}\n|-\n|[[Central Technical School|Central Technical School shooting]] || [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] || September 30 || 2010 || 0 || At least one gunshot was fired from a handgun following a confrontation between four students, causing a victim to suffer a graze wound to his temple. The school was placed under lock down, and two 17-year-olds were charged by police, one with charges related to the shooting, and the other with conspiracy.<ref name=\"High school locked down\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/crime/2010/09/30/high_school_locked_down_after_gun_fired.html |title=High school locked down after gun fired |date=September 30, 2010 |work=Toronto Star |accessdate=April 5, 2013 }}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref name=\"School shooting suspect charged\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/school-shooting-suspect-faces-10-charges-1.873076 |title=School shooting suspect faces 10 charges |work=CBC News |date=October 6, 2010 |accessdate=April 5, 2013 }}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n \n|-\n|Les Racines de vie Montessori || [[Gatineau]], [[Quebec]] || April 5 || 2013 || 2 (including the perpetrator) ||A gunman killed one man and himself at a small daycare. There were 53 children present at the school, which is divided between two houses. Daycare staff at the houses, 225 and 229 Gamelin St., called 911 at 10:27&nbsp;a.m. about a man threatening people. Police arrived and found one man dead with a shotgun beside him, apparently a suicide. A second dead man was found soon after. Police have identified one of the dead as Robert Charron but have not named him the shooter.<ref name=\"Gatineau police ID 1 of 2 dead\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2013/04/05/ottawa-quebec-police-operation-montessori-school.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130405171418/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2013/04/05/ottawa-quebec-police-operation-montessori-school.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=April 5, 2013|title=Gatineau police ID 1 of 2 men dead in daycare shooting|date=April 5, 2013|work=CBC News|accessdate=April 5, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[York University]] shooting || [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] || March 6 || 2014 || 0 || One woman was shot and suffered non-life-threatening injuries and another woman received minor non-gun-related injuries from the suspect during a shooting that took place at the University Student Centre. Kemon Edwards, 22, is alleged to have been carrying a gun that accidentally discharged in the crowded student center around 10:45&nbsp;p.m. during the weekly pub night at the Underground, which is connected to the cafeteria. He faced 17 charges including discharging a firearm, careless use of a firearm and aggravated assault.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.thestar.com/news/crime/2014/03/14/arrest_made_in_york_university_shooting.html | work=Toronto Star | title=Six people arrested in York University shooting |first=Jennifer |last=Pagliaro |date=March 14, 2014 |accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[La Loche shootings]] || [[La Loche]], [[Saskatchewan]] || January 22 || 2016 || 4 || Two people were killed and seven others were injured when a 17-year-old student opened fire inside of the [[La Loche Community School]]. Prior to the school shooting, the suspect shot dead two of his cousins at a home. The suspect was apprehended and is currently in custody.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/la-loche-community-school-lock-down-jan22-1.3416143 | work=CBC Canada | title=5 dead following school shooting in La Loche, Sask., Trudeau says |date=January 22, 2016 |accessdate=January 22, 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Europe===\nThe following is a list of incidents of shootings that occurred at schools in Europe.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Name || Location || Date||Year || Death toll || Notes\n|-Luder\n|[[Bremen school shooting]] || [[Bremen]], Germany || June 20 || 1913 || 5 (4 by gunfire)<ref name=Prager>[http://anno.onb.ac.at/cgi-content/anno?apm=0&aid=ptb&datum=19130621&seite=8&zoom=2 Der Massenmord in der M\u00e4dchenschule], ''[[Prager Tagblatt]]'' (June 21, 1913)</ref> || 29-year-old unemployed teacher Heinz Schmidt indiscriminately shot at students and teachers, killing four girls and wounding more than twenty others before being subdued by school staff. A fifth girl also died during the incident when she fell down a staircase.<ref name=NYT>[https://www.nytimes.com/1913/06/21/archives/kills-3-wounds-17-in-a-classroom-lunatic-had-been-rejected-as-a.html Kills 3, wounds 17 in a classroom], ''[[The New York Times]]'' (June 21, 1913)</ref>\n|-\n|[[Wilno school massacre]] || [[Wilno]], [[Second Polish Republic]]<br />(now Vilnius, Lithuania)|| May 6|| 1925 || 5 (including both perpetrators) || A student of Joachim Lelewel High School, Stanis\u0142aw \u0141awrynowicz, fired shots and detonated a hand grenade which killed him, two students and a teacher while sitting Matura (final exams). His friend, Janusz Obr\u0105balski attempted to detonate another grenade, which turned out to be faulty. Obr\u0105balski then committed suicide by shooting himself in the head. A bomb left by the two was later found in one of the classrooms.\n|-\n|[[Kung\u00e4lv school shooting]] || [[Kung\u00e4lv]], Sweden|| March 4 || 1961 || 1 || A 17-year-old student fired fifteen bullets into a crowd at a school dance at Kung\u00e4lvs L\u00e4roverk (aka Thorildskolan), killing one student and wounding six others before escaping. He turned himself in to local police the following morning and was arrested.\n|-\n|[[Cologne school massacre]] || [[Cologne]], Germany || June 11 || 1964 || 11 (including the perpetrator)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://suche.abendblatt.de:8000/article.php?url=/ha/1964/xml/19640612xml/habxml64_18543.xml|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130210043219/http://suche.abendblatt.de:8000/article.php?url=/ha/1964/xml/19640612xml/habxml64_18543.xml|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 10, 2013|title=Wie lebende Fackeln st\u00fcrzten Kinder ins Freie|publisher=[[Hamburger Abendblatt]]|language=German|date=June 12, 1964}}</ref> || 42-year-old Walter Seifert attacked numerous students and adults with a home-made [[flamethrower]], killing eight students before murdering his last two victims, both female teachers, with a [[spear]]. He then swallowed [[parathion]], and died the following day.\n|-\n|St John's School\n|Dundee, United Kingdom\n|November 1\n|1967\n|1\n|Armed with a shotgun, [[Robert Mone]] entered a girls' needlework class at St John's School. He subjected the 14- and 15-year-old pupils and their pregnant teacher, Nanette Hanson, to a 1\u00bd-hour ordeal, before shooting Hanson dead, raping one girl, and sexually assaulting another.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/tribute-to-teacher-killed-by-monster-mone-961852|title=Tribute To Teacher Killed By Monster Mone|last=Moncur|first=James|date=November 2, 2007|website=dailyrecord|access-date=September 29, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Zadar school shooting || [[Zadar]], [[Yugoslavia]] || October || 1972 || 2 ||19-year-old student Milorad Vulinovi\u0107 shot and killed two of his professors using his father's stolen gun.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zadarskilist.hr/clanci/04102010/38-godina-od-ubojstva-vice-vlatkovica-i-gojka-matuline|title=38 godina od ubojstva Vice Vlatkovi\u0107a i Gojka Matuline|publisher=[[Zadarski list]]|language=Croatian|date=October 4, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Eppstein school shooting]] || [[Eppstein]], Germany || June 3 || 1983 || 6 (including the perpetrator) || 34-year-old Czech refugee Karel Charva opened fire in a sixth-grade classroom, first shooting and wounding the teacher, then killing three students and injuring fourteen others. He then killed a teacher and a police officer who tried to intervene before committing suicide. An additional thirty children suffered from shock during the incident.\n|-\n|Ferres Comprehensive School || [[Higham Ferrers]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom]] || January 6 || 1988 || 0 || Three months after he was expelled, Darren Fowler returned to his former school, Ferres Comprehensive School, shooting and wounding two teachers and two pupils before he was overpowered by staff.<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = The Glasgow Herald | title = Boy Rambo gets life | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2507&dat=19880625&id=8jNAAAAAIBAJ&pg=3452,6976776&hl=en | date = June 25, 1988 | accessdate = December 29, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Raumanmeri school shooting]] || [[Rauma, Finland]] || January 24 || 1989 || 2 || Two students were fatally shot by a 14-year-old student at the Raumanmeri secondary school. The shooter had claimed to be a victim of [[bullying]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/school_shootings_rare_in_finland/5808607|title=School Shootings Rare in Finland|publisher=[[YLE]]|date=November 7, 2007|accessdate=November 7, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Aarhus University shooting]] || [[Aarhus]], Denmark || April 5 || 1994 || 3 (including the perpetrator) || 35-year-old student Flemming Nielsen shot and killed two people and wounded two others with a [[sawed-off shotgun]] before taking his own life.<ref name=\"Drabssager - 1994\">[http://drabssageridanmark.beboer2650.dk/html/drabssager_-_1994.html Drabssager \u2013 1994] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015222910/http://drabssageridanmark.beboer2650.dk/html/drabssager_-_1994.html |date=October 15, 2015 }}(Danish)</ref>\n|-\n|[[Dunblane massacre]] || [[Dunblane]], United Kingdom || March 13 || 1996 || 19 (including the perpetrator and the unborn child) || 43-year-old Thomas Hamilton opened fire in a gymnasium, killing sixteen children and one adult and injuring fifteen others before committing suicide. It remains the deadliest attack on children in British history.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2008/jun/05/tennis.scotland |title=Murray describes fight to cope with trauma of Dunblane school killings |work=The Guardian |location=London |date=June 5, 2008 |accessdate=June 6, 2008 | first=Martin | last=Hodgson}}</ref> \nA [[Firearms (Amendment) (No. 2) Act 1997|ban]] on the ownership of handguns was introduced in the United Kingdom (with the exception of Northern Ireland) following the massacre.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/2609427.stm |title=New Year gun amnesty planned |date=December 27, 2002 |work=BBC News |accessdate=July 14, 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|ROC de Leijgraaf || [[Veghel]], Netherlands || December 7 || 1999 || 0 || A 17-year-old student opened fire at ROC de Leijgraaf school, wounding three students and one teacher. One student was critically injured. It was the first school shooting in the history of the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/554440.stm |newspaper=BBC News |title=Student shoots four at Dutch school |date=December 7, 1999}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/557116.stm |newspaper=BBC News |title=School shooting suspect's family arrested |date=December 9, 1999}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Erfurt massacre]] || [[Erfurt]], Germany || April 26 || 2002 || 17 (including the perpetrator) || 19-year-old Robert Steinh\u00e4user began shooting through his former school, targeting teachers and faculty members. Twelve teachers and one administrator were killed, along with two students and a police officer; only one other person was injured. The shooter then committed suicide.<ref>[http://archives.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/europe/04/27/germany.shooting/ Brave teacher stopped gun rampage], ''CNN'', April 27, 2002 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622190047/http://archives.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/europe/04/27/germany.shooting/ |date=June 22, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Coburg shooting]] || [[Coburg]], Germany || July 3 || 2003 || 1 (the perpetrator) || A 16-year-old student, known only as Florian K., shot and wounded his teacher and an intervening school psychiatrist before taking his own life.<ref name=\"The Independent\">{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/pupil-kills-himself-in-school-shooting-585557.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026025854/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/pupil-kills-himself-in-school-shooting-585557.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 26, 2012|title=Pupil kills himself in school shooting|date=July 3, 2003|accessdate= March 12, 2009| work=[[The Independent]]| location=London| first=Tony| last=Paterson}}</ref>\n|-\n| Terra College || [[The Hague]], Netherlands || January || 2004 || 1 || A student shot the school principal, Hans van Wieren, in the head.\n|-\n| R\u00f6tz school shooting || [[R\u00f6tz]], Germany || March 7 || 2005 || 0 ||After being ordered to leave the classroom, a 14-year-old student returned with a gun and threatened the life of the 35-year-old class teacher. During a struggle the weapon was fired and taken from the student. Investigators' findings state that the student did not intend to kill the teacher, but himself. No one was injured.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/panorama/aus-aller-welt/keine-verletzten-bayrischer-schueler-schiesst-mit-revolver-auf-lehrer/2481506.html|title=Bayrischer Sch\u00fcler schie\u00dft mit Revolver auf Lehrer|publisher=[[Handelsblatt]]|language=German|date=March 7, 2005}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Emsdetten school shooting|Geschwister Scholl School attack]] || [[Emsdetten]], Germany || November 20 || 2006 || 1 (the perpetrator) || 18-year-old Bastian Bosse, a former student of the school, fired several shots with two sawed-off rifles and a [[Caplock mechanism|caplock pistol]] and also threw several homemade [[smoke bomb]]s before killing himself. The incident ended with no other fatalities, with 37 people being injured, including four students who suffered gunshot wounds, one teacher wounded by being hit in the face with a smoke bomb, sixteen police officers who suffered from smoke inhalation, and the school custodian who was shot in the abdomen inside the school.<ref>[http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/0,1518,449557,00.html 18-j\u00e4hriger Amokl\u00e4ufer verteilte Bomben im Schulgeb\u00e4ude] (\"18-year old madman distributed bombs in school building\"), ''[[Der Spiegel|Spiegel Online]]''.</ref>\n|-\n|[[Jokela school shooting]] || [[Tuusula]], Finland || November 7 || 2007 || 9 (including the perpetrator) || 18-year-old Pekka-Eric Auvinen opened fire in the school's main hallway, killing six students, school principal Helena Kalmi, and the school nurse before shooting and wounding himself in a suicide attempt; he later died at a hospital. One other person suffered gunshot wounds, and eleven people were injured by shattering glass while escaping from the school building. The day before the incident, Auvinen posted a video on YouTube predicting the massacre at the school.<ref name=\"CNN\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/europe/11/07/school.shooting/index.html|title=Teen gunman dead from critical injuries who opened fire on Finnish classmates|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=November 7, 2007|accessdate=November 7, 2007| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071109052100/http://www.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/europe/11/07/school.shooting/index.html| archivedate = November 9, 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/7082795.stm|title=Fatal shooting at Finnish school|work=[[BBC News]]|date=November 7, 2007|accessdate=November 7, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kauhajoki school shooting]]|| [[Kauhajoki]], Finland || September 23 || 2008 || 11 (including the perpetrator) || 22-year-old student Matti Juhani Saari entered the school via the basement and opened fire in a classroom he attended before setting it on fire with homemade [[Molotov cocktails]] and then fleeing the scene. Nine students and one staff member died in the incident. A woman was shot in the head and critically wounded, but survived after having two operations, while ten other students sustained minor injuries such as sprains and cuts from broken glass. Authorities eventually found Saari, who had shot himself but was still alive; he died a short time later. It was assumed that the [[Jokela school shooting|Jokela case]], the previous year (above), inspired Saari to commit the massacre.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/23/us-finland-shooting-news-idUSTRE48M92I20080923?feedType=RSS&feedName=topNews|title=Gunman kills 10, self in Finnish school shooting|first=Attila|last=Cser|date=September 23, 2008|accessdate=September 24, 2008 |quote=The killer, 22-year-old Matti Saari, started a fire in the school and then shot himself in the head. He died later in Tampere University Hospital.|work=Reuters}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Winnenden school shooting]]|| [[Winnenden]], Germany || March 11 || 2009 || 16 (including the perpetrator) || 17-year-old Tim Kretschmer, a former student of the school, opened fire in two classrooms and a chemistry laboratory, killing nine and injuring seven others. He then successfully escaped the school, killing two female teachers in the process. Afterwards, he shot and killed the caretaker of a psychiatric facility and then carjacked a motorist, who drove him into another town before escaping unharmed. The shooter opened fire in a car showroom after unsuccessfully trying to steal a car, killing two and injuring two others. He then committed suicide after a brief shootout with police.<ref name=\"BBCWinnenden\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/7936817.stm |title='German school gunman 'kills 15' |accessdate=March 11, 2009 |work=BBC News |date=March 11, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"DWmain\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dw.de/teenage-gunman-takes-own-life-after-german-school-shooting/a-4088804-1 |title= German Police Say School Shooting Kills at Least Nine |accessdate=March 11, 2009 |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]] |date=March 11, 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[OAED Vocational College shooting]]|| [[Athens]], Greece || April 10 || 2009 || 1 (the perpetrator) || 19-year-old Dimitris Patmanidis shot and wounded a student and two workers from a nearby technical company before shooting and wounding himself in the head in a suicide attempt. He died later at a hospital.<ref name=\"BBC-OAED\">{{cite news |authorlink= | title=Greek gunman dies after shooting | date=April 10, 2009 | publisher= news.bbc.co.uk | url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/7993401.stm | work =[[BBC]] | pages = | accessdate = April 10, 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kanebogen School#School shooting|Kanebogen Elementary School shooting]] || [[Harstad]], Norway || April 28 || 2009 || 0 || A nine-year-old student fired a [[shotgun]] in schoolyard; however, nobody was injured in the incident. The shooter was disarmed and subdued by a female teacher, but due to his age, he wasn't tried for the crime, although his father was fined for not keeping the shotgun, a rifle, and ammunition according to Norwegian rules. This was the first Norwegian school shooting.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/nineyearold-fires-shotgun-at-norwegian-school-1675420.html|title=Nine-year-old fires shotgun at Norwegian school|date=April 28, 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[University of P\u00e9cs|University of P\u00e9cs shooting]] || [[P\u00e9cs]], Hungary || November 26 || 2009 || 1 || A 23-year-old student entered the building of the university's biophysics research institute and opened fire in the classroom, killing one man. In earlier reports, two people were reported to be in critical condition and a third in serious condition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pecsinapilap.hu/cikk/Pecsi_egyetemi_lovoldozes_____ma_kezdodik_G_Akos_buntetopere/40218|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110104115604/http://www.pecsinapilap.hu/cikk/Pecsi_egyetemi_lovoldozes_____ma_kezdodik_G_Akos_buntetopere/40218|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 4, 2011|title=P\u00e9csi egyetemi l\u00f6v\u00f6ld\u00f6z\u00e9s \u2013 ma kezd\u0151dik G. \u00c1kos b\u00fcntet\u0151pere|date=December 15, 2010|publisher=P\u00e9csi Napilap}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Toulouse school shooting]] || [[Toulouse]], France || March 19 || 2012 || 5 (including the perpetrator) || 23-year-old Mohammed Merah opened fire at a [[Jewish day school]], killing three schoolchildren and a teacher. The incident was the last of three terrorist attacks against [[French Armed Forces|French soldiers]] and [[Jews|Jewish civilians]], occurring in an eight-day span. The shooter was later shot and killed by police after a massive three-day manhunt and a 30-hour standoff at his home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-17456582|title=Toulouse school shootings traumatise French Jews|first=David|last=Chazan|date=March 22, 2012|website=Bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2014 Moscow school shooting]] || [[Moscow]], Russia || February 3 || 2014 || 2 || High school student Sergey Gordeyev, armed with two rifles, forced his way past a security guard, took hostages, and killed his geography teacher. He then killed a police officer and wounded another who arrived at the scene. He later released the hostages and was captured by the police after his father came to the school.<ref>{{cite news|title=Student gunman kills policeman and teacher in hostage takeover of class of 20 students in school near Moscow |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2550822/BREAKING-NEWS-Gunman-kills-policeman-takes-class-24-teenage-students-hostage-Moscow-school.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail}}</ref> \n|-\n|[[Viljandi school shooting|2014 Viljandi school shooting]] || [[Viljandi]], Estonia || October 27 || 2014 || 1 || A 15-year-old boy killed his German language teacher with a gun in Paalalinna school. All students were evacuated in school hall and police arrested the shooter. As of now, it remains unclear as to why the shooting took place.\n|-\n|[[Barcelona school killing|2015 Joan Fuster school shooting]] || [[Barcelona]], Spain || April 20 || 2015 || 1 || A 13-year-old boy armed with a [[crossbow]] and a [[machete]] killed a teacher and injured 4. The first ever student to organize a school shooting in Spain had a breakdown when his PE teacher managed to talk with him, then proceeded to sit in a classroom until the police arrived. Under Spanish law, the boy is exempt from legal responsibility because he's under 14.\n|-\n|Tocqueville high school shooting || [[Grasse]], France || March 16 || 2017 || 0 || Kylian Barbey, a 17-year-old boy, armed with a [[rifle]], two [[handguns]], a [[revolver]] and two [[grenades]] opened fire at Alexis de Tocqueville high school. A total of four were injured, three students and the school's principal. Anti-terrorist commandos were sent to the scene and the shooter was arrested. The perpetrator's [[Facebook]] and [[YouTube]] accounts showed that he was interested in the [[Columbine Massacre]] and watched videos on how to make homemade weapons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-39292755|title=France school shooting: Teenage boy arrested after four hurt |date=March 16, 2017|publisher=[[bbc.co.uk]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|Shadrinsk school shooting || [[Shadrinsk]], Russia || March 21 || 2018 || 0 || A 13-year-old girl opened fire with a gas pistol at her school in Russia's Kurgan region, injuring seven seventh graders. The victims suffered bruises and scrapes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/russia-kurgan-school-shooting/29112975.html|title=Russian Schoolgirl Shoots Classmates With Gas Pistol, Seven Injured |date=March 21, 2018 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|Barabinsk college shooting || [[Barabinsk]], Russia || May 10 || 2018 || 1 (the perpetrator) || A college student shot another student with a double-barreled shotgun and shot himself.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.segodnya.ua/world/russia/teper-ya-nad-vami-podshuchu-poyavilis-detali-strelby-uchenika-v-rossii-1137103.html | title=\"\u0422\u0435\u043f\u0435\u0440\u044c \u044f \u043d\u0430\u0434 \u0432\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0448\u0443\u0447\u0443\": \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0431\u044b \u0432 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0435}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kerch Polytechnic College massacre]]|| [[Kerch]], Crimea || October 17 ||2018 || 21 (including the perpetrator) || A [[bomb]] exploded on the first floor and then Vladislav Roslyakov, an 18-year-old boy, started shooting people in the college's dining room on the second floor. A total of 21 people died and over 50 people were injured.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45891201|title=Crimea attack: College shooting kills 19|work=BBC News|date=October 17, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019 Brze\u015b\u0107 Kujawski school attack || [[Brze\u015b\u0107 Kujawski]], Poland || May 27 || 2019 || 0 || 18-year-old former student known only as Marek N. detonated explosives then he shot and wounded 2 people<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.se.pl/wiadomosci/polska/strzelanina-w-brzesciu-kujawskim-kim-jest-sprawca-marek-n-aa-pXiB-Up7q-SWTP.html |title = Strzelanina w Brze\u015bciu Kujawskim. Kim jest sprawca, Marek N.?}}</ref> in apparent [[Columbine High School massacre|Columbine]]-style attack at W\u0142adys\u0142aw \u0141okietek Elementary School.\n|-\n|}\n\n===Mexico===\nThe following is a list of incidents of shootings that occurred at schools in Mexico.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Name !! Location !! Date !! Year !! Death toll !! Notes\n|-\n| Iztapalapa school shooting || Mexico City, Mexico || May 13 || 2004 || 1 || A 13-year-old middle-schooler, Alejandro, accidentally shot classmate, Dalia G\u00f3mez, in the head at Instituto Angel del Campo. The wound caused a significant neurological injury and immediately left her in a coma. She was later declared brain dead and died a week later in a hospital. Alejandro allegedly took the gun to school to show it to his friends.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jornada.unam.mx/2004/05/18/042n1soc.php?printver=1&fly=|title=Declaran con muerte cerebral a la menor baleada; no hay esperanzas de que se recupere|date=May 18, 2004|work=[[La Jornada]]|accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref>\n|- \n| Ciudad Nezahualc\u00f3yotl school shooting || [[Ciudad Nezahualc\u00f3yotl]], Estado de M\u00e9xico || February 7 || 2005 || 0 || A middle-school student accidentally shot a female classmate in the leg with a .25 caliber weapon. She was not reported in critical condition.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archivo.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/431972.html|title=Evidencia asesinato en colegio deficiente control de armas|date=June 19, 2007|work=[[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]]|accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref>\n|- \n| Winston Churchill school shooting || Mexico City, Mexico || June 13 || 2007 || 1 || Fernando Marcelo Mart\u00ednez Gonz\u00e1lez, a father of a student, entered the school near the time that the school was supposed to start. He shot and killed the preschool principal Carla Jim\u00e9nez Ba\u00f1os with a 9&nbsp;mm<!--The reference says .9, but you can't buy bullets that small, and if you could, I can't imagine it killing a human. 9 mm ammo is common. --> pistol. This came after the school let Fernando and his ex-wife know that they would not allow their son to go to the school because they believed that the situation at home was affecting other students as well.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jornada.unam.mx/2007/06/14/index.php?section=capital&article=038n1cap|title=Consterna asesinato de directora de escuela en la Guadalupe Inn|date=June 14, 2007|work=[[La Jornada]]|accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Chihuahua School Shooting || [[Chihuahua City|Chihuahua]], [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] || October 1 || 2010 || 2 (including the perpetrator) || When 2 policemen attended a call of a violent argument in Primaria Benito Juarez, they were forced to put their weapons down after the perpetrator took the vice-principal hostage and aimed a gun at her head. Soon after, he murdered her and he committed suicide after being surrounded by officials.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.elsiglodetorreon.com.mx/noticia/562945.ex-policia-arma-balacera-en-escuela-de-chihuahua.html|title=Ex polic\u00eda arma balacera en escuela de Chihuahua|date=October 1, 2010|work=[[El Siglo de Torre\u00f3n]]|accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez school shooting || [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]], [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] || August 24 || 2011 || 1 || Two cars drove up to an elementary school at around noontime, as parents were waiting for their children to be released from school. The men in the cars started firing assault rifles, killing one man, and wounding four women and one man. The elementary school was placed on lock-down and students were released after the situation was being handled. While the motive of the attack is reported to be unknown, schools in the Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez area have reported receiving threats and extortion demands in the past.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/08/25/one-dead_n_936045.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212064022/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/08/25/one-dead_n_936045.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=December 12, 2013|title=1 Dead, 5 Wounded In Mexico Border School Shooting|date=August 25, 2011|work=[[Huffington Post]]|accessdate=September 12, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez school shooting || Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez, Chihuahua || January 12 || 2012 || 1 || A 30-year-old man was killed by being shot nine times in front of children at an elementary school as they were leaving for the day. The shooting induced panic from parents of children, some of whom witnessed the shooting. The gunman was unidentified, as of 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/01/12/world/americas/mexico-school-homicide/index.html|title=Man gunned down at elementary school in Juarez|date=January 12, 2012|work=[[CNN]]|accessdate=September 12, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| Atizap\u00e1n school shooting || Atizap\u00e1n de Zaragoza, Estado de M\u00e9xico || May 6 || 2014 || 1 || 13-year-old Ricardo Ordonez was shot and killed at a school. 15-year-old \u00c9dgar Yoevani was arrested.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lapoliciaca.com/nota-roja/de-un-balazo-mata-joven-de-15-anos-a-companero-en-salon-de-clases/|title=De un balazo mata joven de 15 a\u00f1os a compa\u00f1ero en sal\u00f3n de clases|date=May 6, 2014|work=La Policiaca|accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n| Monterrey school shooting || Monterrey, Nuevo Le\u00f3n|| January 18 || 2017 || 2 (including the perpetrator) || [[Colegio Americano del Noreste 2017 shootings]] 15-year-old Federico Guevara Elizondo committed suicide after shooting 2 students and a teacher. The teacher died more than 2 months later in hospital.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2017/03/29/world/americas/ap-lt-mexico-school-shooting.html|title=Mexico: Teacher Wounded in January School Shooting Dies|date=March 29, 2017|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=April 3, 2017}}{{dead link|date=May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Conalep 106 school shooting || [[Azcapotzalco]], Mexico City || March 25 || 2017 || 0 ||A teenage student accidentally shot a classmate.<ref>{{cite news |title=Estos son algunos tiroteos registrados en escuelas de M\u00e9xico |url=https://noticieros.televisa.com/historia/tiroteos-escuelas-mexico-alumnos-estudiantes-balacera/ |accessdate=20 January 2020 |work=Noticieros Televisa |date=10 January 2020 |language=es-MX}}</ref>\n|-\n| UNAM school shooting || Mexico City, Mexico || February 23 || 2018 || 2 || 2 drug dealers that operated within the [[University City of Mexico|Ciudad Universitaria]] were apparently shot by two drug dealers from opposing cartels. The two victims, of ages 20 and 29, died the same day in a medical clinic. They had no relation to the institution.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/comunidad/2018/02/24/1222482|title=Balacera en la UNAM|date=February 24, 2018|work=[[Exc\u00e9lsior]]|accessdate=February 28, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Los Mochis school shooting || Los Mochis, Sinaloa || February 25 || 2018 || 1 || An armed group of hitmen approached Joel Medina, director of operations at the local police department and law student at the time at [[Autonomous University of Sinaloa]], and shot him to death inside his vehicle while arriving to the parking lot of the university's installations. The suspects were later engaged in a gunfight against police forces and 2 hitmen were allegedly killed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.m-x.com.mx/2018-02-25/sicarios-matan-a-director-de-la-policia-de-ahome-en-las-instalaciones-de-la-facultad-de-derecho-de-la-universidad-de-sinaloa/|title=Sicarios matan a director operativo de polic\u00eda|date=February 25, 2018|website=M-X.com.mx|accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Huixquilucan school shooting || Huixquilucan, Estado de M\u00e9xico || April 11 || 2018 || 0 || After a heated discussion between two students at Telesecundaria No. 0399 \"Lic. Alfredo del Mazo\", a student pulled out a pistol and shot at the stomach of another student. The perpetrator fled the scene to his home where he committed suicide as he was believed to be in extreme regret. The victim survived the attack.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.proceso.com.mx/529583/estudiante-de-telesecundaria-del-edomex-dispara-a-un-companero-huye-y-luego-se-suicida|title=Estudiante de telesecundaria del Edomex dispara a un compa\u00f1ero, huye y luego se suicida|date=April 22, 2018|work=[[Proceso (magazine)|Proceso]]|accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Cd. Victoria school shooting || [[Ciudad Victoria]], Tamaulipas || April 24 || 2018 || 1 || At Preparatoria Federalizada No. 1 \"Marte R. G\u00f3mez\", a failed kidnapping attempt led an unknown number of shooters to descend from a vehicle and shoot at students inside the school facility. 3 males, one of them dead, and 2 females were shot.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2018/04/25/actualidad/1524623469_323034.html|title=Tiroteados cinco estudiantes en un instituto de bachillerato de Ciudad Victoria|date=April 24, 2018|work=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|accessdate=April 25, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Nicolas Romero school shooting || Ciudad Nicol\u00e1s Romero, Estado de Mexico || February 12 || 2019 || 1 || The events occurred in the Juana de Asbaje middle school in municipality ofCiudad Nicol\u00e1s Romero, located in the outskirts of Mexico city. A 13-year-old boy was shot by accident by a classmate who was demonstrating a .22 caliber pistol to him. The student was taken into custody by local authorities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tribuna.com.mx/seguridad/Por-accidente-un-menor-asesina-de-un-balazo-a-su-companero-20190213-0016.html|title=Por accidente, un menor asesina de un balazo a su compa\u00f1ero|date=February 13, 2019|work=[[Tribuna]]|accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| San Andr\u00e9s Huaxpaltepec school shooting || San Andr\u00e9s Huaxpaltepec, Oaxaca || February 21 || 2019 || 1 || At an elementary school in a small community in the southern regions of the state of Oaxaca, gunmen entered the installation and killed a teacher at gunpoint in front of some of the school's students. The reasons of why he was targeted are unknown.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.debate.com.mx/mexico/Asesinan-a-balazos-a-maestro-enfrente-de-sus-alumnos-en-Oaxaca-20190221-0184.html|title=Asesinan a balazos a maestro enfrente de sus alumnos en Oaxaca|date=February 21, 2019|work=[[Debate]]|accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| UAZ school shooting || Zacatecas, Zacatecas || April 10 || 2019 || 1 || A 22-year-old student was shot 8 times by one gunman. The attack was targeted directly at her.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.milenio.com/policia/matan-a-estudiante-dentro-de-la-universidad-autonoma-de-zacatecas|title=Matan a tiros a alumna dentro de Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Zacatecas|date=April 10, 2019|work=[[Milenio]]|accessdate=April 30, 2019|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Colegio Cervantes shooting]] || [[Torre\u00f3n]], Coahuila || January 10 || [[2020 in Mexico|2020]] || 2 (including the perpetrator) || An 11-year-old student used two guns to shoot two teachers and three students, killing one teacher and himself.<ref>[https://www.proceso.com.mx/613652/torreon-alumno-mata-a-una-maestra-y-hiere-a-cuatro Alumno mata a una maestra y hiere a cuatro personas en colegio de Torre\u00f3n, luego se suicida] By Maria Luisa Vivas, Proceso, Jan 10, 2020</ref> The school periodically participates in ''Operativo Mochila'' (Operation Backpack), and it is unclear how he got the guns into the school.<ref>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/tiroteo-en-colegio-deja-2-muertos-en-torre-n-coahuila Tiroteo en colegio deja 2 muertos en Torre\u00f3n, Coahuila] Diario de Morelos, Jan 10, 2020</ref> The newspaper ''El Universal'' reported that the shooter was influeced by a video game and had stated on a [[Facebook]] group that he wanted to duplicate the 2017 Monterrey school shooting.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/videojuego-natural-selection-influyo-al-menor-del-tiroteo-del-colegio-cervantes Videojuego \"Natural Selection\" influyo al menor del tiroteo: gobernador] El Universal, Jan 10, 2020</ref> He was dressed in a white T-shirt and suspenders, reminiscent of Eric Harris in the [[Columbine High School massacre]].<ref>[https://aristeguinoticias.com/1001/multimedia/alumno-de-torreon-uso-vestimenta-semejante-a-la-de-un-autor-de-la-matanza-de-columbine-en-1999-video/ Alumno de Torre\u00f3n us\u00f3 vestimenta semejante a la de un autor de la matanza de Columbine en 1999] Aristegui Noticias, Jan 10, 2020</ref>\n|}\n\n===Oceania===\nThe following is a list of incidents of shootings that occurred in the [[Oceania|Oceanic]] region.